content: eToro business is based on CFD's, what is basically your bet against their. You won't be able to buy/sell your shares at market openings, during times of high volatility or they'll sell your stock when they start losing. You agree with that by accepting T&C. You don't have any shareholder rights like voting, or dividend in form of shares (cash only) even if you buy "real asset". That means they don't really buy your shares or they are lent to short sellers (another form of bet against you).
replyContent: Hi Pawel, we're sorry to read this review of us. Information about owning stocks can be found on our help center. We're not responsible for market availability during volatility because of the trading disruptions. Find out more here https://www.etoro.com/trading/disruptions/ We'd be happy to expand further if you decide to contact our CS team. MJ

content: I regret that I didn't do my own research before opening an account with Etoro. Firstly, I deposited $5000 via Bpay to my account but I never received it. After a week they sent me a notification said that I had to fill in a form before they could put the money in my account. So I did. Then they asked me to provide 3 month bank statement before putting that $5000 in my account. I didn't feel comfortable to do so and told them to send the money back to where it was from. Again, they said they had sent it back but I never received it. When I asked them, they asked for my bank statement showing this transfer. What a joke, if I didn't made the transfer, how could you receive the money? But I still cooperated and sent them the statement. After that they provided me with some ref numbers and told me to ask my bank. When I was about to call my bank, I found the money reached my account. It had been almost 2 months since I made the deposit. Guess how long it would take if you wanted to withdraw money. Also, like other reviewers said, you don't 'own' the shares and cryptos you purchased with your own money. They will close the trade 'on your behalf' whenever they want, that is , when the rates are at all time low due to the war. Now i am going to ASIC and AFCA to lodge complaint against them.
replyContent: We're sorry to hear about your experience. Withdrawals are typically processed within 2 business days & time it takes to receive them depends on your payment service provider.
